\"height:0.1514em;\">\u003Cspan style=\"top:-2.55em;margin-left:0em;margin-right:0.05em;\">\u003Cspan class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\">\u003C/span>\u003Cspan class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\">\u003Cspan class=\"mord mathnormal mtight\">n\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003Cspan class=\"vlist-s\">​\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003Cspan class=\"vlist-r\">\u003Cspan class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.15em;\">\u003Cspan>\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003Cspan class=\"mclose\">)\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003C/td>\u003C/tr>\u003Ctr>\u003Ctd>CA\u003C/td>\u003Ctd>Discrete\u003C/td>\u003Ctd>Discrete\u003C/td>\u003Ctd>Game of Life\u003C/td>\u003C/tr>\u003C/tbody>\u003C/table>\n\u003Ch2 id=\"neural-applications\">Neural Applications\u003C/h2>\n\u003Cp>Neural networks can be viewed as dynamical systems where:\u003C/p>\n\u003Cul>\n\u003Cli>\u003Cstrong>State\u003C/strong>: Activities of all neurons\u003C/li>\n\u003Cli>\u003Cstrong>Dynamics\u003C/strong>: Evolution according to connection weights and inputs\u003C/li>\n\u003Cli>\u003Cstrong>Attractors\u003C/strong>: Stable patterns representing memories or decisions\u003C/li>\n\u003C/ul>",{"headings":21,"localImagePaths":32,"remoteImagePaths":33,"frontmatter":34,"imagePaths":35},[22,26,29],{"depth":23,"slug":24,"text":25},2,"formal-definition","Formal Definition",{"depth":23,"slug":27,"text":28},"types","Types",{"depth":23,"slug":30,"text":31},"neural-applications","Neural Applications",[],[],{"title":14},[],"dynamical-system.md","manifold",{"id":37,"data":39,"body":41,"filePath":42,"digest":43,"rendered":44,"legacyId":58},{"title":40},"Manifold","A **manifold** is a topological space that locally resembles Euclidean space near each point. \n\nMore precisely, an $n$-dimensional manifold is a space where every point has a neighborhood that can be mapped homeomorphically to an open subset of $\\mathbb{R}^n$.\n\n## Key Properties\n\n- **Local flatness**: Zoom in enough, and it looks like $\\mathbb{R}^n$\n- **No self-intersections** (for embedded manifolds)\n- Can be curved globally while remaining smooth locally\n\n## Examples\n\n- A sphere $S^2$ is a 2-manifold\n- A circle $S^1$ is a 1-manifold\n- The configuration space of a robot arm is often a manifold\n\nIn neural dynamics, the state of a population of neurons often evolves on a low-dimensional manifold embedded in the high-dimensional activity space.","src/content/concepts/manifold.md","dc6d69ea52b62bd7",{"html":45,"metadata":46},"\u003Cp>A \u003Cstrong>manifold\u003C/strong> is a topological space that locally resembles Euclidean space near each point.\u003C/p>\n\u003Cp>More precisely, an \u003Cspan class=\"katex\">\u003Cspan class=\"katex-mathml\">\u003Cmath xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\">\u003Csemantics>\u003Cmrow>\u003Cmi>n\u003C/mi>\u003C/mrow>\u003Cannotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">n\u003C/annotation>\u003C/semantics>\u003C/math>\u003C/span>\u003Cspan class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\">\u003Cspan class=\"base\">\u003Cspan class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.4306em;\">\u003C/span>\u003Cspan class=\"mord mathnormal\">n\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003C/span>-dimensional manifold is a space where every point has a neighborhood that can be mapped homeomorphically to an open subset of \u003Cspan class=\"katex\">\u003Cspan class=\"katex-mathml\">\u003Cmath xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\">\u003Csemantics>\u003Cmrow>\u003Cmsup>\u003Cmi mathvariant=\"double-struck\">R\u003C/mi>\u003Cmi>n\u003C/mi>\u003C/msup>\u003C/mrow>\u003Cannotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\mathbb{R}^n\u003C/annotation>\u003C/semantics>\u003C/math>\u003C/span>\u003Cspan class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\">\u003Cspan class=\"base\">\u003Cspan class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6889em;\">\u003C/span>\u003Cspan class=\"mord\">\u003Cspan class=\"mord mathbb\">R\u003C/span>\u003Cspan class=\"msupsub\">\u003Cspan class=\"vlist-